The paper deals with content-based image retrieval (CBIR) of medical images, which is a task related to computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves the use of autoencoders, which are a type of neural network and fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and deep learning (cs.DL). The paper also mentions the use of local binary patterns (LBP), which is a popular feature extraction technique in computer vision and multimedia (cs.MM).
